{
  "stem": "21626.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But not one parent had such a thoughtful idea as those diaries and the contacts with the sun and the stars.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It really-- I think it preserved my sanity and my optimism and my faith, you know.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I didn't stay with the, with Auntie Marjorie terribly long because the Rainfords felt they were responsible for me.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And also Dorothy, who was a very outspoken young lady, clashed with Auntie Marjorie no end.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And when I went into the isolation hospital, she couldn't face a whole month of Auntie Marjorie on her own without me.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And she went home, pleading that she also had to be in quarantine because she was in contact with me.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she never, ever returned.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And as Liverpool was being extensively bombed, the Rainfords rented a house in Ainsdale, which was also part of Southport.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then we could be together again.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not immediately, because it was about six months before they, they moved out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then, then I went to live with them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then [SIGHS] after Dunkirk it was when many Czech solders fled, and airmen fled together with the president in exile, President Benes, from France to Britain.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the government in exile was set up in London.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And lots of their families came as well.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then I sort of felt, I shall have Czech soldiers fighting at the side of the British, you know, for our freedom.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it seemed a very important [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] role that they had to play.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that first Christmas after Dunkirk, 1940, 1940, I wrote to President Benes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I expressed my faith in him that he would lead us into a free Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I got a little visiting card back from him in acknowledgement.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
